public class hello {

	public static void main(String[] args) {
		int x = 7;
		int y = 5;
		int a = 5;
		int b = 9;

		// Logical AND: true && true => true
		boolean result1 = x > y && a < b; // true && true => true âœ…
		System.out.println("result1: " + result1);

		// Logical OR: true || true => true
		boolean result2 = x > y || a < b; // true || true => true âœ…
		System.out.println("result2: " + result2);

		// Logical AND: true && false => false
		boolean result3 = x > y && a > b; // true && false => false âŒ
		System.out.println("result3: " + result3);

		// Logical OR: true || false => true
		boolean result4 = x > y || a > b; // true || false => true âœ…
		System.out.println("result4: " + result4);

		// Logical AND: false && true => false
		boolean result5 = x < y && a < b; // false && true => false âŒ
		System.out.println("result5: " + result5);

		// Logical OR: false || true => true
		boolean result6 = x < y || a < b; // false || true => true âœ…
		System.out.println("result6: " + result6);

		// Logical OR: false || true || true => true
		boolean result7 = x < y || a < b || a > 1; // false || true || true => true âœ…
		System.out.println("result7: " + result7);

		// Logical NOT: a > b => 5 > 9 => false => !false => true
		boolean result8 = a > b; // false âŒ
		System.out.println("result8: " + !result8); // !false => true âœ…
	}
}

âœ… Java Logical Operators â€“ Important Interview Points
ðŸ”¹ AND (&&)

    Short-circuits if first condition is false.

    Use when both conditions must be true.

    E.g., Login: usernameCorrect && passwordCorrect

ðŸ”¹ OR (||)

    Short-circuits if first condition is true.

    Use when any one condition should be true.

    E.g., Discounts: isStudent || isSeniorCitizen

ðŸ”¹ NOT (!)

    Flips the boolean value.

    Use for negation or reverse logic.

    E.g., !isLoggedIn means user is not logged in.
